11 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
12 An Act relating to schools; defining terms; requiring
each school district and charter school to conduct
13 certain audit, remove certain books or materials, and
submit to the State Department of Education certain
14 listing annually by certain date; requiring
submission of certain attestation; requiring certain
15 catalog to be publicly accessible; prohibiting
certain library from purchasing or having certain
16 books or other materials; providing certain
construction; providing process for reporting
17 suspected violations; providing for notification;
requiring a public meeting within certain time period
18 under certain circumstances; requiring certain
advance meeting notice; requiring public comment;
19 providing for appeal to the State Department of
Education; requiring certain investigation and
20 notification of investigation findings; allowing a
school district or charter school to request certain
21 hearing within certain time period; directing the
State Board of Education to review certain
22 information and vote on certain determination;
authorizing certain designation of a school for
23 certain noncompliance; providing graduated penalty
for noncompliance; providing for promulgation of
